Text: We cannot become desensitized to the mass shootings that take place too frequently in our country. Yesterday 10 innocent victims were killed by a hate-filled shooter; today more were murdered in California. My heartfelt condolences to each family touched by these tragedies.

I am outraged by today's Senate vote that failed to advance the Women's Health Care Protection Act, a bill that would protect legal abortion nationwide. A woman's right to choose is a basic right. As Congresswoman, I will fight to protect the rights of all.https://t.co/P0MrzmBQDO
This is a fundamental right that ensures women are not treated as second class citizens. In Congress, I will do everything in my power to codify these rights. https://t.co/UPWlXW2YVX

Last night we learned that the Supreme Court is preparing to overturn Roe v. Wade - dismantling 50 years of rights given to women to make their own healthcare decisions and choose what happens to their bodies. https://t.co/mvYLeVfEw8
